entries.journal_entry_completion_summary: You located a courier satchel from the Battle of Naboo that contained a Gungan Record Bauble and managed to get it decoded for Broma Lak.
entries.journal_entry_description: Broma Lak's client believes that some critical information about the Gungan Hydrostatic technology was lost during the Battle of Naboo.  He has hired you to locate it for him.
entries.task00_journal_entry_description: Broma Lak wants you to locate a courier satchel that was last seen during the Battle of Naboo. He has reason to believe that it was recently seen near Theed in the possession of a devious looking Ankura Gungan.
entries.task01_comm_message_text: Good. I was right to trust you with this. Find the kaadu nesting ground and search the mounds there.
entries.task01_journal_entry_description: Comm from Broma Lak: "Good. I was right to trust you with this. Find the kaadu nesting ground and search the mounds there."
entries.task02_journal_entry_description: Comm from Broma Lak: "Good. I was right to trust you with this. Find the kaadu nesting ground and search the mounds there."
entries.task03_journal_entry_description: Though it is covered in Kaadu filth, you have apparently located the courier pouch that Captain Lak is looking for.
entries.task04_journal_entry_description: You have discovered a filth encrusted courier satchel that looks like it might have been sitting in that Kaadu mound since the Battle of Naboo.  Bring it to Broma Lak near Theed.
entries.task05_journal_entry_description: Broma Lak's constitution prohibits handling anything as befouled as the satchel you found.  Search through it and bring him whatever you find.
entries.task06_journal_entry_description: You found an old-fashioned Gungan record bauble secreted in the filthy courier satchel. This is exactly the sort of thing Broma Lak is looking for! Bring it to him near Theed.
